  "prompt": "Should you rinse with water after mouthwash?",
  "response": "It's generally recommended not to rinse your mouth with water immediately after using mouthwash, especially if it contains fluoride. Rinsing can wash away the beneficial ingredients in the mouthwash that help protect your teeth and gums. To maximize the benefits, it's best to wait at least 30 minutes before rinsing with water or eating/drinking anything after using a fluoride mouthwash. However, if you're using a mouthwash that doesn't contain fluoride, you may not need to worry as much, but it still depends on the specific product and your oral health needs. Always check the instructions on the mouthwash label for the best guidance.",
